<!DOCTYPE frameset SYSTEM "frameset.dtd">
<frameset>
    <predicate lemma="jump">
        <note>
            Frames file for 'jump' based on survey of initial sentences of big
            corpus and comparison with 'increase'
        </note>
        
        <roleset id="jump.01" name="stock prices" vncls="45.6">
            <roles>
                <role descr="thing jumping" n="1">
                    <vnrole vncls="45.6" vntheta="Patient"/>
                </role>
                <role descr="EXT, amount jumped by" n="2">
                    <vnrole vncls="45.6" vntheta="Extent"/>
                </role>
                <role descr="start point" n="3"/>
                <role descr="end point or end state of arg1" n="4"/>
            </roles>
            
            <example name="">
                <text>
                    Cray Research stock jumped $2.875 yesterday to close at $38.
                </text>
                <arg n="1">Cray Research stock</arg>
                <rel>jumped</rel>
                <arg n="2">$2.875</arg>
                <arg f="TMP" n="m">yesterday</arg>
                <arg n="4">to close at $38</arg>
            </example>
            
            <note>
                Recall from 'rise' and 'gain' etc that arg2 can also be a MNR, as in
                &quot;jumped sharply&quot;.
            </note>
            
        </roleset>
        
        <roleset id="jump.02" name="be excited for an opportunity" vncls="-">
            <roles>
                <role descr="jumper" n="0"/>
                <role descr="opportunity" n="1"/>
            </roles>
            
            <example name="opportunity knocks">
                <text>
                    Several new funds have jumped to trade at big premiums.
                </text>
                <arg n="0">Several new funds</arg>
                <rel>jumped</rel>
                <arg n="1">to trade at big premiums</arg>
            </example>
            
        </roleset>
        
        <roleset id="jump.03" name="physically or metaphorically leap" vncls="51.3.2">
            <roles>
                <role descr="jumper" n="0">
                    <vnrole vncls="51.3.2" vntheta="Theme"/>
                </role>
            </roles>
            
            <example name="leap">
                <text>
                    John jumped off the roof.
                </text>
                <arg n="0">John</arg>
                <rel>jumped</rel>
                <arg f="DIR" n="m">off the roof</arg>
            </example>
            
            <example name="metaphorical">
                <text>
                    And what we want *PRO* to do *T* is we-3 do n't want *PRO*-3 to just look
                    at the meterial evidence that we have *T* and immediately make a -- um
                    jumpt to a conclusion that this is a certain individual.
                </text>
                <arg n="0">*PRO*</arg>
                <arg n="m" f="ADV">just</arg>
                <arg n="m" f="TMP">immediately</arg>
                <arg n="m" f="DIS">um</arg>
                <rel>jump</rel>
                <arg f="DIR" n="m">to conclusions</arg>
            </example>
            <note>
                predicate edited by Arrick
            </note>
            
        </roleset>
        
        
        <roleset id="jump.06" name="to escape, bail out" vncls="51.3.2">
            <roles>
                <role descr="entity escaping" n="0">
                    <vnrole vncls="51.3.2" vntheta="Agent"/>
                </role>
                <role descr="entity escaped from (e.g. bail/trail); or idiomatically
    'jump ship'" n="1">
                    <vnrole vncls="51.3.2" vntheta="Theme"/>
                </role>
            </roles>
            
            <example name="jump ship">
                <text>
                    She is jumping ship.
                </text>
                <arg n="0">She</arg>
                <rel>jumping</rel>
                <arg n="1">ship</arg>
            </example>
            <note> Most examples in this roleset are pretty idiomatic: "jump ship"
                means to bail out of something, or literally to leave a sinking ship; "jump bail" means to fail to appear in
                court after posting bail. These are all being lumped together in one
                roleset. Edited by Miriam. 
            </note>
        </roleset>
        
        <roleset id="jump.07" name="various idioms" vncls="-">
            <roles>
                <role descr="jumper" n="0"/>
                <role descr="idiomatic expression" n="1"/>
            </roles>
            
            <example name="jump the gun">
                <text>
                    Now all of these statements by the President and others are jumping the gun.
                </text>
                <arg n="m" f="DIS">Now</arg>
                <arg n="0">all of these statments by the President and others</arg>
                <rel>jumping</rel>
                <arg n="1">the gun</arg>
            </example>
            <note>
                predicate added by Arrick
            </note>
            
        </roleset>
        
        
    </predicate>
    
    <predicate lemma="jump_in">
        <note>
            basically the same as &quot;be excited at an opportunity&quot; roleset
        </note>
        
        <roleset id="jump.04" name="opportunity" vncls="-">
            <roles>
                <role descr="jumper" n="0"/>
                <role descr="opportunity" n="1"/>
            </roles>
            
            <example name="knock knock">
                <text>
                    People are jumping in now to buy the funds.
                </text>
                <arg n="0">People</arg>
                <rel>[jumping] [in]</rel>
                <arg f="TMP" n="m">now</arg>
                <arg n="1">to buy the funds</arg>
            </example>
            
            <note>
            </note>
            
        </roleset>
    </predicate>
    
    <predicate lemma="jump_up">
        <note>
            to rise quickly in excitement
        </note>
        
        <roleset id="jump.05" name="rise" vncls="-">
            <roles>
                <role descr="jumper" n="0"/>
            </roles>
            
            <example name="rise quickly">
                <inflection person="ns" tense="ns" aspect="ns" voice="ns" form="ns"/>
                <text>
                    He jumped up from his seat.
                </text>
                <arg n="0">He</arg>
                <rel>[ jumped] [ up]</rel>
                <arg n="M" f="DIR">from his seat</arg>
            </example>
            
            <note>
                Jump_up and 'Jump ship' added by Miriam.
            </note>
            
        </roleset>
    </predicate>
</frameset>




